			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: MB, kill in PoI, Need Help/info<a name="35697"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 21 04 5:32 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Agree with most of what Mose says apart from this bit:
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Others may have a difference of opinion but I recommend centering MB in his room as opposed to cornering him. Once MT has aggro and has called attack call it is max DPS time. MB must die quickly or the spiders will wipe you. Dead in 30seconds or so is ideal. Casters should belly cast on him to avoid ping pong.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
MB casts an AE silence (range 100) so I suggest putting MB in the corner, casters and healers at the opposite corner. Casters won't do much dps once the unresistable silence hits em.
<br />

<br />
Spiders groups - you can handle these with ~3-4 people, so if you're short on raid forces don't use a full group per corner. I suggest killing rather than trying to mezz/kite etc, as its much safer and controlled. Pre-arrange replacements so the spider groups can get flags/loot drops etc once MB dies. I found shaman/monk/any dps worked well for spiders. The good thing is you can setup the spider groups early and leave em for 5-10 minutes to check they can handle the situation. Only move into MB room when you're 100% confident they can manage.
<br />

<br />
With regard to the linked strat, gear and AAs etc have probably improved a lot, and the requirements are way OTT these days unless you're talking a pure open raid of low levels without AAs or decent gear. 40 people, 3 clerics, 2 enchanters, 4 patchers would suffice. Uber guilds can probably get away with much less than that even.
<br />

<br />
Obviously everyone has their own method - whether you chose to mezz/kite/kill spiders is up to you and will depend a bit on numbers and class balance. 
<br />

<br />
Final words: Don't forget the AE silence, and DPS is key.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
