				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: MB, kill in PoI, Need Help/info<a name="35739"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 21 04 12:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've now led 2 raids on MB and won both.  First we had over 50 second was around 40.  He's kind of a chump for us now.  Here are my recommendations -- don't commit more than 2 people per corner.  You can hold a corner with one enchanter and one shaman.  A single bard who knows how to kite can hold a corner by him/herself.  For the actual assault, just jump him and jump him hard - center, corner, don't matter.  With the AEs he throws, especially the silence, agro is going to go all over and it's hard to keep him in any one spot without taking 20 seconds to build agro and corner him which is a fatal tactic since every extra second you spend fighting him means more spiders stretching your enchanters to the breaking point on the corners.  I put two tanks including one paladin for sure in the main tank group with a bard.  That bard puretones and sings Psalm of Veeshan -- NOTHING ELSE!!!!!  If you try to twist, when the silence hits no one has any resist protection and this guy has mean AEs for every single resist.  I keep casters at the door to the room where they can duck out into the hall between casts.  Last fight, the silence went off early but after that we resisted Biomelt IV 4 times in a row and he died in 37 seconds.  I then punched Giwin the gnome, ran him outside into the corner and faded, went back to the room and discovered 4 dead people.  Four.  And this raid was entirely non-elemental flagged folks.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
