				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: MB, kill in PoI, Need Help/info<a name="36139"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 23 04 11:37 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One of the details people don't discuss often:  the impression created is that the spiders walk into the room and instantly explode for 2K+.  This is not the case.  What happens is that several spiders walk into the room, they walk over to one of the machines along the walls and gather around it, then they ALL explode for 2K+ each.
<br />

<br />
So if you see a spider walking in you probably have time to run out, drag a corpse out, etc. before he goes boom.
<br />

<br />
If I had 8 enchanters and 4 bards in a raid, I would consider the strat proposed above, but really that's an amazing complement of people.  You need 2 bards INSIDE the room doing resists -- one doing Psalm of Veeshan for the main tank and one doing AOE for everyone else -- whether that one does Elemental Chorus or Purifying Chorus, he will miss some of the possible AEs -- MB has 6 AEs and they cover all 5 resist types.  He doesn't use all 6 in every fight, but you never know what resists you really need.  MR is definitely good but beyond that, its a crap shoot.  I will say that in doing many MB raids and leading the last 2, I have NEVER had spiders make it to the doors during the actual MB fight and that is with ONE enchanter or ONE bard per corner (and maybe a backup healer with them).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Dinngo Derringer<br>
